Open Bidding for Government Purchase Gains Popularity
SHENZHEN , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- The financial bureau in Shenzhen , China 's first special economic zone , in Guangdong Province has saved 70 million yuan ( about eight million U.S. dollars ) since the introduction of open bidding for government car purchasing in November 1997 .
The bureau has accepted bids for a number of purchase items , including facilities , services and engineering projects .
The city government has allocated 500 million yuan , or 50 percent of its fiscal budget , for open and fair purchases .
A government official said that reform of purchasing practices has achieved anticipated results , including reducing expenditures , increasing the transparency of purchasing procedures and curbing corruption .
